cards.name: Bulbasaur
cards.description: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

cards.name: Ivysaur
cards.description: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

cards.name: Venusaur

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.description: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

attacks.name: Giant Bloom
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.effect: Put 1 random {G} Pokémon from your deck into your hand.

cards.description: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

cards.name: Metapod
cards.description: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

cards.name: Butterfree

abilities.name: Powder Heal
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokémon.

cards.description: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

cards.name: Weedle
cards.description: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

cards.name: Kakuna
cards.description: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.

cards.name: Beedrill
cards.description: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

cards.name: Oddish
cards.description: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

cards.name: Gloom
cards.description: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

cards.name: Vileplume

attacks.name: Soothing Scent
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.description: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

cards.name: Paras
cards.description: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

cards.name: Parasect
cards.description: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

cards.name: Venonat
cards.description: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokémon at night that are attracted by light.

cards.name: Venomoth

attacks.name: Poison Powder
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.description: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

cards.name: Bellsprout
cards.description: Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.

cards.name: Weepinbell
cards.description: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

cards.name: Victreebel

abilities.name: Fragrance Trap
abilities.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, once during your turn, you may switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Basic Pokémon to the Active Spot.

cards.description: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

cards.name: Exeggcute
cards.description: Though it may look like it's just a bunch of eggs, it's a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

cards.name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Stomp
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

cards.description: Each of Exeggutor's three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don't seem to be very interested in one another.

attacks.name: Tropical Swing
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

cards.name: Tangela

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.effect: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.description: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon's true appearance remains a mystery.

cards.name: Scyther
cards.description: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

cards.name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Double Horn
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

cards.description: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

cards.name: Cottonee
cards.description: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

cards.name: Whimsicott
cards.description: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

cards.name: Petilil

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.effect: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.description: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.

cards.name: Lilligant

attacks.name: Leaf Supply
attacks.effect: Take a {G} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched {G} Pokémon.

cards.description: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.

cards.name: Skiddo

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.description: Until recently, people living in the mountains would ride on the backs of these Pokémon to traverse the mountain paths.

cards.name: Gogoat
cards.description: It can sense the feelings of others by touching them with its horns. This species has assisted people with their work since 5,000 years ago.

cards.name: Charmander

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.effect: Discard a {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

cards.name: Charmeleon
cards.description: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

cards.name: Charizard

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.effect: Discard 2 {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

attacks.name: Crimson Storm
attacks.effect: Discard 2 {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.name: Vulpix

attacks.name: Tail Whip
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

cards.description: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

cards.name: Ninetales

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.effect: Discard 1 {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

cards.name: Growlithe
cards.description: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

cards.name: Arcanine

attacks.name: Heat Tackle
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

cards.description: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

attacks.name: Inferno Onrush
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

cards.name: Ponyta
cards.description: It can't run properly when it's newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

cards.name: Rapidash
cards.description: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

cards.name: Magmar
cards.description: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

cards.name: Flareon

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.effect: Discard 1 {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

cards.name: Moltres

attacks.name: Sky Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.description: It's one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

attacks.name: Inferno Dance
attacks.effect: Flip 3 coins. Take an amount of {R} Energy from your Energy Zone equal to the number of heads and attach it to your Benched {R} Pokémon in any way you like.

cards.name: Heatmor
cards.description: There's a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

cards.name: Salandit
cards.description: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

cards.name: Salazzle
cards.description: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

cards.name: Sizzlipede
cards.description: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

cards.name: Centiskorch

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.effect: Discard a {R} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

cards.name: Squirtle
cards.description: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

cards.name: Wartortle
cards.description: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

cards.name: Blastoise

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra {W} Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

cards.description: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

attacks.name: Hydro Bazooka
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra {W} Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

cards.name: Psyduck

attacks.name: Headache
attacks.effect: Your opponent can't use any Supporter cards from their hand during their next turn.

cards.description: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

cards.name: Golduck
cards.description: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.

cards.name: Poliwag
cards.description: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon's innards showing through the skin.

cards.name: Poliwhirl
cards.description: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl's has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

cards.name: Poliwrath

abilities.name: Counterattack
abilities.effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, do 20 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.

cards.description: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

cards.name: Tentacool
cards.description: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

cards.name: Tentacruel

attacks.name: Poison Tentacles
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.description: When the red orbs on Tentacruel's head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

cards.name: Seel
cards.description: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don't bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

cards.name: Dewgong
cards.description: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

cards.name: Shellder
cards.description: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

cards.name: Cloyster

abilities.name: Shell Armor
abilities.effect: This Pokémon takes -10 damage from attacks.

cards.description: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

cards.name: Krabby
cards.description: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

cards.name: Kingler

attacks.name: KO Crab
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

cards.description: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

cards.name: Horsea
cards.description: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

cards.name: Seadra

attacks.name: Water Arrow
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

cards.description: It's the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

cards.name: Goldeen
cards.description: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

cards.name: Seaking

attacks.name: Horn Hazard
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.description: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

cards.name: Staryu
cards.description: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you'll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

cards.name: Starmie
cards.description: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

cards.name: Magikarp
cards.description: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

cards.name: Gyarados

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.effect: Discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

cards.name: Lapras

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has at least 3 extra {W} Energy attached, this attack does 70 more damage.

cards.description: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

cards.name: Vaporeon

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

cards.description: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin, which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

cards.name: Omanyte
cards.description: Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people, this species is becoming a problem.

cards.name: Omastar

attacks.name: Ancient Whirlpool
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't attack.

cards.description: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn't move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

cards.name: Articuno

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.description: It's said that this Pokémon's beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.effect: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

cards.name: Ducklett
cards.description: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

cards.name: Swanna
cards.description: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

cards.name: Froakie
cards.description: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

cards.name: Frogadier
cards.description: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

cards.name: Greninja

abilities.name: Water Shuriken
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may do 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

cards.description: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

cards.name: Pyukumuku
cards.description: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

cards.name: Bruxish

attacks.name: Second Strike
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

cards.description: It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by this process from the protuberance on its head.

cards.name: Snom
cards.description: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow, so it will eat its way up a mountain, aiming for the peak.

cards.name: Frosmoth

attacks.name: Powder Snow
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.description: Frosmoth senses air currents with its antennae. It sends its scales drifting on frigid air, making them fall like snow.

cards.name: Pikachu
cards.description: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

cards.name: Raichu

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.effect: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

attacks.name: Circle Circuit
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched {L} Pokémon.

cards.name: Magnemite
cards.description: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

cards.name: Magneton

abilities.name: Volt Charge
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may take a {L} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

cards.description: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

cards.name: Voltorb
cards.description: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

cards.name: Electrode
cards.description: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

cards.name: Electabuzz

attacks.name: Thunder Punch
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage. If tails, this Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

cards.description: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

cards.name: Jolteon

attacks.name: Pin Missile
attacks.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

cards.description: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

cards.name: Zapdos

attacks.name: Raging Thunder
attacks.effect: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.description: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

attacks.name: Thundering Hurricane
attacks.effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

cards.name: Blitzle
cards.description: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

cards.name: Zebstrika

attacks.name: Thunder Spear
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

cards.description: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

cards.name: Tynamo
cards.description: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

cards.name: Eelektrik
cards.description: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

cards.name: Eelektross

attacks.name: Thunder Fang
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.description: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

cards.name: Helioptile
cards.description: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon's electric moves.

cards.name: Heliolisk

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

cards.description: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.

cards.name: Pincurchin

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.description: This Pokémon generates electricity when it digests food. It uses its five hard teeth to scrape seaweed off surfaces and eat it.

cards.name: Clefairy
cards.description: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

cards.name: Clefable
cards.description: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

cards.name: Abra

attacks.name: Teleport
attacks.effect: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.description: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra's dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

cards.name: Kadabra
cards.description: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

cards.name: Alakazam

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

cards.name: Slowpoke
cards.description: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

cards.name: Slowbro
cards.description: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

cards.name: Gastly
cards.description: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body, slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

cards.name: Haunter
cards.description: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

cards.name: Gengar

attacks.name: Bother
attacks.effect: Your opponent can't use any Supporter cards from their hand during their next turn.

cards.description: To steal the life of its target, it slips into the prey's shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

abilities.name: Shadowy Spellbind
abilities.effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't use any Supporter cards from their hand.

cards.name: Drowzee
cards.description: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.

cards.name: Hypno

abilities.name: Sleep Pendulum
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.description: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

cards.name: Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Barrier Attack
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes -20 damage from attacks.

cards.description: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

cards.name: Jynx

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: Its strange cries sound like human language. There are some musicians who compose songs for Jynx to sing.

cards.name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Power Blast
attacks.effect: Discard 2 {P} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.description: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene-splicing and DNA-engineering experiments.

attacks.name: Psydrive
attacks.effect: Discard 2 {P} Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.name: Ralts
cards.description: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people's emotions.

cards.name: Kirlia
cards.description: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

cards.name: Gardevoir

abilities.name: Psy Shadow
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may take 1 {P} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to the {P} Pokémon in the Active Spot.

cards.description: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

cards.name: Woobat
cards.description: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it's evidence that Woobat live there.

cards.name: Swoobat
cards.description: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won't be able to fly for a little while.

cards.name: Golett
cards.description: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

cards.name: Golurk

attacks.name: Double Lariat
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

cards.description: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

cards.name: Sandshrew
cards.description: It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

cards.name: Sandslash
cards.description: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon's spikes will feel when touched.

cards.name: Diglett
cards.description: It lives about one yard underground, where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

cards.name: Dugtrio

attacks.name: Dig
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.

cards.description: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby, making it easier for it to burrow.

cards.name: Mankey
cards.description: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

cards.name: Primeape

attacks.name: Fight Back
attacks.effect: If this Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

cards.description: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

cards.name: Machop
cards.description: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

cards.name: Machoke
cards.description: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

cards.name: Machamp
cards.description: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

cards.name: Geodude
cards.description: Geodude that have lived a long life have had all their edges smoothed out until they're totally round. They also have a calm, quiet disposition.

cards.name: Graveler
cards.description: It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came.

cards.name: Golem

attacks.name: Double-Edge
attacks.effect: This Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

cards.description: When Golem grow old, they stop shedding their shells. Those that have lived a long, long time have shells green with moss.

cards.name: Onix
cards.description: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

cards.name: Cubone

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.effect: During your opponent’s next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do −20 damage.

cards.description: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

cards.name: Marowak
cards.description: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

attacks.name: Bonemerang
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

cards.name: Hitmonlee

attacks.name: Stretch Kick
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

cards.description: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

cards.name: Hitmonchan
cards.description: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

cards.name: Rhyhorn
cards.description: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

cards.name: Rhydon
cards.description: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

cards.name: Kabuto
cards.description: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.

cards.name: Kabutops

attacks.name: Leech Life
attacks.effect: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.

cards.name: Mienfoo
cards.description: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

cards.name: Mienshao
cards.description: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

cards.name: Clobbopus
cards.description: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

cards.name: Grapploct

attacks.name: Knock Back
attacks.effect: Switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

cards.description: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

cards.name: Ekans
cards.description: By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.

cards.name: Arbok

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

cards.description: The latest research has determined that there are over 20 possible arrangements of the patterns on its stomach.

cards.name: Nidoran♀

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.effect: Put 1 random Nidoran♂ from your deck onto your Bench.

cards.description: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they'll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

cards.name: Nidorina
cards.description: The horn on its head has atrophied. It's thought that this happens so Nidorina's children won't get poked while their mother is feeding them.

cards.name: Nidoqueen

attacks.name: Lovestrike
attacks.effect: This attack does 50 more damage for each of your Benched Nidoking.

cards.description: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

cards.name: Nidoran♂
cards.description: The horn on a male Nidoran's forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

cards.name: Nidorino
cards.description: With a horn that's harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

cards.name: Nidoking

attacks.name: Poison Horn
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.description: When it goes on a rampage, it's impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it's lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

cards.name: Zubat
cards.description: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

cards.name: Golbat
cards.description: It loves to drink other creatures' blood. It's said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it's gathered.

cards.name: Grimer

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.description: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

cards.name: Muk

attacks.name: Venoshock
attacks.effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 50 more damage.

cards.description: It's thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

cards.name: Koffing
cards.description: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

cards.name: Weezing

abilities.name: Gas Leak
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Poisoned.

cards.description: If one of the twin Koffing inflates, the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.

cards.name: Mawile

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

cards.name: Pawniard
cards.description: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch, it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.

cards.name: Bisharp
cards.description: This Pokémon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.

cards.name: Meltan

attacks.name: Amass
attacks.effect: Take 1 {M} Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

cards.description: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

cards.name: Melmetal

abilities.name: Hard Coat
abilities.effect: This Pokémon takes -20 damage from attacks.

cards.description: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

cards.name: Dratini
cards.description: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process, it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

cards.name: Dragonair
cards.description: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body, the weather will begin to change instantly.

cards.name: Dragonite

attacks.name: Draco Meteor
attacks.effect: 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is chosen at random 4 times. For each time a Pokémon was chosen, do 50 damage to it.

cards.description: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

cards.name: Pidgey
cards.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

cards.name: Pidgeotto
cards.description: The claws on its feet are well developed. It can carry prey such as an Exeggcute to its nest over 60 miles away.

cards.name: Pidgeot

abilities.name: Drive Off
abilities.effect: Once during your turn, you may switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

cards.description: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

cards.name: Rattata
cards.description: Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life. If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.

cards.name: Raticate
cards.description: People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.

cards.name: Spearow
cards.description: Its reckless nature leads it to stand up to others—even large Pokémon—if it has to protect its territory.

cards.name: Fearow

attacks.name: Drill Run
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.description: Carrying food through Fearow's territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!

cards.name: Jigglypuff
cards.description: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

cards.name: Wigglytuff
cards.description: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry, or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.

attacks.name: Sleepy Song
attacks.effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

cards.name: Meowth

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.effect: Draw a card.

cards.description: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

cards.name: Persian

attacks.name: Shadow Claw
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

cards.description: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

cards.name: Farfetch'd
cards.description: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

cards.name: Doduo
cards.description: A two-headed Pokémon that was discovered as a sudden mutation. It runs at a pace of over 60 miles per hour.

cards.name: Dodrio
cards.description: An enemy that takes its eyes off any of the three heads—even for a second—will get pecked severely.

cards.name: Lickitung

attacks.name: Continuous Lick
attacks.effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

cards.description: If this Pokémon's sticky saliva gets on you and you don't clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won't go away, either.

cards.name: Chansey
cards.description: This kindly Pokémon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

cards.name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Dizzy Punch
attacks.effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

cards.description: Although it's carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

cards.name: Tauros
cards.description: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it's a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

cards.name: Ditto

attacks.name: Copy Anything
attacks.effect: Choose 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon’s attacks and use it as this attack. If this Pokémon doesn’t have the necessary Energy to use that attack, this attack does nothing.

cards.description: Its transformation ability is perfect. However, if made to laugh, it can't maintain its disguise.

cards.name: Eevee
cards.description: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

attacks.name: Primal Wingbeat
attacks.effect: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon into their deck.

cards.description: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

cards.name: Snorlax
cards.description: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

cards.name: Minccino
cards.description: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

cards.name: Cinccino

attacks.name: Do the Wave
attacks.effect: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

cards.description: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

cards.description: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

cards.name: Dubwool
cards.description: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.effect: During your opponent’s next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do −20 damage.
